<h3 id="3-rock-bottom">3 Rock bottom</h3>

<p>I was frustrated, and was defintely planning to give up.</p>

<p>But then, one day a City University engineering student replied to my debugging question, and for whatever reason, my program is working alongside the electronics. The sensor could send data straight to my computer.</p>

<p>I started to gain momentum, finished my Machine Learning algorithm. It was the closest I felt to the end goal, to actually building and launching Nung.</p>

<h3 id="4-success">4 SUCCESS</h3>

<p>And I was right, after 4 months of pain, hard work, and countless of failures, I have finally finished <strong>Nung</strong>.</p>

<p>I have soldered the lithium polymer battery to my electronics, did a user test.</p>

